How to install tensorflow-gpu1.13.31 on

Dell G7 || RTX2070

1. First install. ubuntu18.04.06
2. Install gcc> sudo install gcc make
3. sudo apt install build-essential
4. Install Nvidia driver (install from sofwtware update): 470.182
		Check: nvidia-smi
check avialble driver: ubuntu-drivers 
5. Install Anaconda: Anaconda3-2023.03-1-Linux-x86_64.sh
6. Install python 3.7
	>>sudo apt update 
	>>sudo apt install software-properties-common
	>>sudo add-apt-repository ppa:deadsnakes/ppa
	>>sudo apt install python3.7
	check
	>>python3.7 --version

7.conda create -n dl python=3.7
8.conda activate dl
9.conda install tensorflow-gpu=1.13.1

.............Done....................
10. Check if tensorflow detect the gpu device or not
>>python
	>>from tensorflow.python.client import device_lib
	>>print(device_lib.list_local_devices())




































